<TITLE> Sahara vows Sunny's killers will face justice </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 8 (bdnews24.com)  Home minister Sahara Khatun on Friday expressed her grief over the death of Bangladesh Chhatra Maitree leader Rezanur Chowdhury Sunny in a n attack by Bangladesh Chhatra League and vowed to bring the perpetrators to justice. "We will not tolerate any act of indiscipline or terrorism," she told reporters after attending a function at Kotbari of Uttarkhaan area of her constituency in Uttara, where she distributed warm clothes among the poor. On Thursday, Sunny was killed by activists of pro-ruling Awami League Chhatra League activists at Rajshahi Polytechnic Institute. "Immediately after the incident, I ordered law-enforcing agencies to find out the responsible persons whoever they might be. Afterwards, some of the people suspected of being involved in the killing were arrested." She also inaugurated a hospital -- JABS Complex -- at Dakkhinkhan area of Uttara. bd
